    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-06T09:29:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-06T09:29:00-05:00" n="566"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d566">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 701.6261/11</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Moscow</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PDC1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Poole</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d566fn2">Sent via the Embassy in France (No. 4411); by
                        wireless from Moscow to Paris.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-06T19:00:00+04:31">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 6, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received July 9, 4.10 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>702. Urgent for Secretary’s attention. <persName>Smith</persName> of the
                    Associated Press has just learned from an authoritative source that the German
                    Ambassador, <persName corresp="#p_MWCv1">Count Mirbach</persName>, was
                    assassinated between 2 and 3 this afternoon at his Embassy. Two persons arriving
                    in machine threw bomb through window. Ambassador and Captain König wounded.
                    Ambassador died in few minutes. Two arrests so far. <persName>Smith</persName>
                    asks that Associated Press be informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PDC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Poole</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
